`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The decomposition strategy varies by file context:
- Standalone `foo.ts` → create `foo/` directory, move content to sub-files, create `index.ts` barrel, **delete** `foo.ts` (TypeScript prefers files over directories when both exist)
- Files already inside a directory (`game/actions/GameActions.ts`) → create sub-files + `index.ts` in same dir, replace original with `export * from "./index"`
- Test files importing `"./foo.ts"` (explicit extension) → update to `"./foo"` so directory resolution works
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
